From: conda-forge
Subject: [PATCH] Explicitly pass package database to Cabal.registerPackage

When using a different bootstrap GHC version, the package database needs
to be explicitly passed to the register command. Without this, the
registration might go to the wrong database or fail to update the cache.

The copyPackage function already passes --target-package-db explicitly,
but registerPackage was relying on the builddir config which may not
work correctly on Windows with version mismatches.

This patch adds explicit --package-db to the register command.

diff --git a/hadrian/src/Hadrian/Haskell/Cabal/Parse.hs b/hadrian/src/Hadrian/Haskell/Cabal/Parse.hs
--- a/hadrian/src/Hadrian/Haskell/Cabal/Parse.hs
+++ b/hadrian/src/Hadrian/Haskell/Cabal/Parse.hs
@@ -188,9 +188,11 @@ registerPackage context@Context {..} = do
     putProgressInfo $ "| Register package " ++ quote (pkgName package)
     ctxPath <- Context.contextPath context
     gpd <- pkgGenericDescription package
+    pkgDbPath <- packageDbPath stage
     verbosity <- getVerbosity
     let v = if verbosity >= Loud then "-v3" else "-v0"
     traced "cabal-register" $
         C.defaultMainWithHooksNoReadArgs C.autoconfUserHooks gpd
-            [ "register", "--builddir", ctxPath, v ]
+            [ "register", "--builddir", ctxPath, "--package-db", pkgDbPath, v ]
+
 -- | What type of file is Main
